Class DoubleSortedList<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<T>
public class DoubleSortedList<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends DoubleLink<T>
A simple linked sorted list structure of T objects. Only the T value contained in the sorted list is visible through the standard sorted list methods. Extends the DoubleLink class, which already defines the front node, rear node, length, isEmpty, and iterator.
Version:
2019-01-26

    • clean

      public void clean()
      Removes duplicates from this List. The list contains one and only one of each value formerly present in this List. The first occurrence of each value is preserved.

    • combine

      public void combine​(DoubleSortedList<T> source1, DoubleSortedList<T> source2)
      Combines contents of two lists into a third. Values are alternated from the source lists into this List, but the sorted order is preserved. The source lists are empty when finished. NOTE: value must not be moved, only nodes.
      Parameters:
      source1 - The first list to combine with this List.
      source2 - The second list to combine with this List.

    • split

      public void split​(DoubleSortedList<T> target1, DoubleSortedList<T> target2)
      Splits the contents of this List into the target Lists. Moves nodes only - does not move value or call the high-level methods insert or remove. this List is empty when done. The first half of this List is moved to target1, and the last half of this List is moved to target2. If the resulting lengths are not the same, target1 should have one more element than target2.
      Parameters:
      target1 - The first List to move nodes to.
      target2 - The second List to move nodes to.

    • splitAlternate

      public void splitAlternate​(DoubleSortedList<T> target1, DoubleSortedList<T> target2)
      Splits the contents of this List into the target Lists. Moves nodes only - does not move value or call the high-level methods insert or remove. this List is empty when done. Nodes are moved alternately from this List to target1 and target2.
      Parameters:
      target1 - The first List to move nodes to.
      target2 - The second List to move nodes to.
